events.name: Google Cloud Auckland -  Stuff talking about their journey to GCP
events.description:
This is the monthly Google Cloud Auckland meetup.

For the October meetup we'll kick off with some GCP updates and then the team from Stuff.co.nz will talk us through their journey to GCP. They will share some of the war stories and lessons learnt during the move of the Stuff mobile home page onto Google cloud using the Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE)

The topics from Stuff will include:
- Motivation of Moving to GKE on GCP
- The Stuff Mobile Homepage Technology Stack
- Kubernetes in GCP
- Overview of Infrastructure Architecture (GCP/GKE/K8)
- Demo
- Our Go Live! Journey
- Q&A

5:30 - Networking, drink and nibbles
6:00 - Presentations
7:00 - Networking
7:30 - End
